  "notes": [
    "This is a virtual time synchronization protocol designed for testing LLM protocol reverse engineering capability",
    "Fixed length 32 bytes, all messages share the same boundary structure",
    "Uses big-endian byte order",
    "Similar to NTP protocol design, containing timestamps and stratum information",
    "Contains request/response message types, supporting both sync and delay measurement modes",
    "CRC16 uses CCITT polynomial (0x1021)",
    "Timestamp is split into seconds (8 bytes) and nanoseconds (4 bytes), providing high-precision time"
